node.text:
Re-wiring your anxious brain is not an easy task thats for sure…
〰️
If you struggle with anxiety, chances are you’re thought patterns are full of Automatic Negative Thoughts (ANTs)...
〰️
It’s time we learn how to reframe these anxious thoughts and retrain our anxious brain!
〰️
To re-wire the anxious brain, it is important to become aware of the irrational thought cycle and change your thinking patterns.
〰️
So instead of letting your anxious thoughts and feelings drive your behavior, practice becoming more aware of triggers related to your thoughts, feelings, and behaviors and restructure your irrational thoughts patterns. 
〰️
This is what we call in the CBT world...Cognitive restructuring.
〰️
Cognitive restructuring is a process of recognizing, challenging, and changing cognitive distortions and negative thought patterns.
〰️
*Recommend: seek help from a trained cognitive behavioral therapist when doing this healing work (remember: CBT isn’t for everyone, so make sure to find the treatment that is best for you)
〰️
Have you ever tried CBT? Which distorted thought patterns can you relate to the most? Comment below ⬇️⬇️⬇️

Photo shared by The Anxiety Healer on September 14, 2021 tagging @theanxietyhealer. May be an image of text that says 'What is it like? "I overthink which stops me from sleeping as just can't switch off." "The worst is when it turns into panic attacks where my chest tightens. feel like I can't breathe and get night sweats." "The next day I'm drained, can barely function and just find it hard to get up which then sets back my entire day." @theanxietyhealer'.

Photo shared by The Anxiety Healer on September 14, 2021 tagging @theanxietyhealer. May be an image of text that says 'Tools that can help Weighted Blanket Weighted blankets can reduce anxiety in both adults and children because their weight gently pushes down on you, reducing the levels of the stress hormone cortisol in your body. Research has also shown that they help reduce autonomic arousal, which is what causes symptoms of anxiety such as increased heart rate. @theanxietyhealer'.

Photo shared by The Anxiety Healer on September 14, 2021 tagging @theanxietyhealer. May be an image of text that says 'Tools that can help Develop a Nighttime Routine Create a nighttime that works best for you and your needs! For some it may be meditation, but for others it's as simple as taking a bubble bath before bed, lighting a scented candle, petting your cat, or reading a good book. What's important is that you take some time to wind down. @theanxietyhealer *Remember to limit your time with electronic devices before bed. These devices give off a harsh, artificial light that can trick your body into staying up longer.'.

Photo shared by The Anxiety Healer on September 14, 2021 tagging @theanxietyhealer. May be an image of text that says 'Tools that can help Sleep Story, Audible, or Podcast Listening to a story as you try to fall asleep can help your brain focus on a calming visualization rather than loud, anxious thoughts. If you were ever read to as a child, you know that there's definitely something comforting about being read to as you doze off for the night. @theanxietyhealer'.

Photo shared by The Anxiety Healer on September 14, 2021 tagging @theanxietyhealer. May be an image of text that says 'Tools that can help Exercise This is one of the most effective way to quickly lower stress hormones in the body that promote both physical and mental health. We're built to move, not sit for hours in front of a computer or TV. Limit strenuous exercise to the morning or early afternoon. @theanxietyhealer'.

Photo shared by The Anxiety Healer on September 14, 2021 tagging @theanxietyhealer. May be an image of text that says 'Tools that can help Aromatherapy Essential oils have been known to improve pain levels and relieve stress. Research shows that lavender oil is one essential oil that's generally considered a natural sleep aid. @theanxietyhealer'.

Photo shared by The Anxiety Healer on September 14, 2021 tagging @theanxietyhealer. May be an image of text that says 'Tools that can help Some Tea! Give up Coffee & Drink Try drinking some chamomile tea before bed! Why? Well, it's commonly called a mild tranquilizer and has an antioxidant called apigenin, which binds to specific receptors in your brain that may decrease anxiety and help make you sleepy. @theanxietyhealer'.

Have you ever heard of healing anxiety with a “savoring walk?”
〰️
This is one of my favorite ways to get out of my head and into the present moment…
〰️
Whenever I begin to ruminate with anxious thoughts, I get up and go outside for a walk. It’s can be for 5 minutes or 5 hours, but it never fails to break me out of those loud negative thoughts patterns.
〰️
If you are reading this and feeling anxious, get up and go outside…take a walk if you can. If not, just breath in the fresh air and pay attention to all of the sights and sounds around you. What do you see? What do you hear?
〰️
You are safe right in this moment…
〰️
Tag someone you would go on a savoring walk with and leave a comment on where you would love to take a savoring walk ⬇️⬇️⬇️
〰️
